        "special_abilities": [
            {
                "type": "stat_block_section",
                "subtype": "special_ability",
                "name": "Elusive",
                "ability_type": "Supernatural",
                "ability_type_abbrev": "Su",
                "text": "A cerberus worm is rarely encountered unless it wishes to be. As a full-round action while in water, a cerberus worm can move up to its run speed (300 feet) without leaving any sign of its passing, as though affected by a <i>pass without trace</i> spell. An elusive cerberus worm gains a +40 circumstance bonus on its Stealth check. In addition, except when in combat, a cerberus worm is considered to be under the effects of a <i>nondetection</i> spell. Both of these spell effects function at caster level 20th and cannot be dispelled."
            },
